posts.title: For those of you that don't understand why Trump is targeting Canada and Mexico
posts.content:
The tariffs from his previous administration are still in place and we are raking in billions in taxes. Democrats never removed them because they are a good source of revenue. The problem is that Both Mexico and Canada are taking advantage of importing Chinese goods and reselling them to the US.

In essence, they are circumventing and even benefitting from a large percentage of Trumps previous tariffs on China. (they are basically laundering goods from China to avoid the tax and selling them at a discount while still making big profit).

Further, both countries allow China to store steel and other commodities in massive stockpile warehouses. They just sit on the goods and collect more and more until there's an artificial shortage and then the price goes up.

Once American industries take out loans and retool to meet the increased demand due to the goods being more scarce and profitable, China floods the market and puts the US industries out of business.

Then, there's the illegal labor they are importing right thru their countries. The cartel profits off this human trafficking.

Lastly, they are allowing China to use them as mules for Fentanyl.

There's a massive trade war with China and by Mexico and Canada's actions, they are not on our side.

posts.title: Why Trumps tariffs are gonna be great for us, explained in a way you can share with anyone.
posts.content:
The idiots in the media keep saying everything is going to go up 25% and they couldn't be more wrong. Take for example something that Canada or Mexico is selling something for $100, and it has been undercutting the price of the American version priced at $105. They've been able to do this because they don't pay as much for labor and avoiding tariffs allows them to undercut American producers.

.

The media is claiming you will now have to pay $125 for the same thing but is ignoring the fact that you still have the American version to buy at $105. Yes it is a short-term 5% increase in this example, but the immense increase in business for the American producers will create an economy of scale and drive the price down perhaps well below the $100 that Canada had been charging. The end result will be a $90 product produced in America and you will end up saving money. More employment domestically. More revenue. The rising tide will lift all of us up.
